		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Euler's formula</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<dl>
<dd><i>This article is about Euler's formula in</i> <a href="/wiki/Complex_analysis" title="Complex analysis">complex analysis</a><i>. For Euler's formula in algebraic topology and polyhedral combinatorics see <a href="/wiki/Euler_characteristic" title="Euler characteristic">Euler characteristic</a>. See also <a href="/wiki/List_of_topics_named_after_Leonhard_Euler" title="List of topics named after Leonhard Euler">topics named after Euler</a>.</i></dd>
</dl>
